WEBVTT

00:03.084 --> 00:06.217
ACCORDING TO THIS MAN'S FAMILY,
HE WAS NOT A SMOKER.

00:06.217 --> 00:09.050
BUT THE TRUTH IS,
HE SMOKED TWO PACKS A DAY

00:09.050 --> 00:10.551
IN HIS CAR FOR 20 YEARS

00:10.551 --> 00:12.893
WHILE HIS WIFE AND CHILDREN
SLEPT.

00:12.893 --> 00:15.806
SOMETIMES THE PATIENT'S SHAME
IS THE ELEPHANT IN THE ROOM.

00:15.806 --> 00:17.228
THEY TRY TO HIDE IT FROM US.

00:17.228 --> 00:18.979
BUT YOU CAN'T HIDE
FROM A SURGEON,

00:18.979 --> 00:20.311
BECAUSE THE BODY DOESN'T LIE.

00:20.311 --> 00:23.444
THE TRUTH IS RIGHT HERE,
FOR EVERYONE TO SEE.

00:23.444 --> 00:27.108
AND IT DOESN'T NEED TO SAY
A SINGLE WORD.

00:29.860 --> 00:34.365
SO, UH...DeLUCA AND I
ARE BASICALLY NOT TALKING.

00:36.036 --> 00:37.868
JUST LIKE YOU TWO.

00:37.868 --> 00:39.250
ONLY DIFFERENT.

00:39.250 --> 00:41.001
OBVIOUSLY.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

00:41.001 --> 00:42.373
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

00:45.005 --> 00:46.377
YEAH, I MEAN,
WE SAY "HI,"

00:46.377 --> 00:49.009
BUT, UH...
THERE'S NO TALKING.

00:49.009 --> 00:52.173
I MEAN,
AFTER THE AMAZING SEX.

00:53.384 --> 00:55.846
ONCE YOU'VE HAD THAT,

00:55.846 --> 00:59.100
YOU WOULD THINK IT WOULD BE
EASIER TO HAVE A CONVERSATION.

01:05.946 --> 01:07.738
SO...

01:07.738 --> 01:10.321
THAT WOMAN STARTS TODAY --
THE RESIDENT FROM DILLARD.

01:10.321 --> 01:12.453
DO YOU WANT TO TALK
ABOUT THAT?

01:12.453 --> 01:14.155
'CAUSE YOU SHOULD.

01:18.409 --> 01:20.040
IT DOESN'T BURN WHEN I PEE
ANYMORE.

01:22.002 --> 01:23.124
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

01:36.477 --> 01:38.219
IT'S YOUR FIRST DAY.
H-HOW DO YOU -- HOW --

01:38.219 --> 01:40.141
IT'S OKAY.

01:40.141 --> 01:41.892
YOU DON'T
HAVE TO DO THAT.

01:41.892 --> 01:43.314
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

01:48.149 --> 01:49.530
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

01:53.824 --> 01:55.616
HI.

01:55.616 --> 01:57.618
CAN YOU GUYS TELL ME HOW TO
FIND OUT WHOSE SERVICE I'M ON?

01:58.739 --> 02:00.120
I MEAN, WHICH ATTENDING?

02:00.120 --> 02:01.952
YOU SHOULD ASK HER.

02:01.952 --> 02:05.416
I'M PROBABLY NOT QUALIFIED
TO ANSWER THAT.

02:05.416 --> 02:07.168
JUST CHECK YOUR E-MAIL.

02:09.420 --> 02:11.051
THANK YOU.

02:11.051 --> 02:13.214
AS YOU KNOW,
TRANSFER RESIDENTS

02:13.214 --> 02:14.885
TRADITIONALLY DO
THEIR FIRST ROTATION

02:14.885 --> 02:17.097
WITH THE CHIEF OF
GENERAL SURGERY, WHICH IS YOU,

02:17.097 --> 02:19.890
AND, AS YOU ALSO KNOW,
OUR NEWEST TRANSFER,

02:19.890 --> 02:23.314
PENELOPE BLAKE,
IS STARTING TODAY.

02:23.314 --> 02:27.318
SO...YOU UNDERSTAND HOW THIS...
COULD HAVE HAPPENED --

02:27.318 --> 02:28.569
WHAT IS "THIS"?

02:28.569 --> 02:31.322
DR. BLAKE
IS ON YOUR SERVICE.

02:31.322 --> 02:35.696
HOWEVER, UM, DR. WEBBER
HAS OFFERED TO TAKE OVER.

02:35.696 --> 02:37.738
OR I CAN.
YOU JUST SAY THE WORD.

02:37.738 --> 02:39.540
I'LL TAKE BLAKE.

02:39.540 --> 02:40.701
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

02:40.701 --> 02:42.833
I'M CHIEF OF GENERAL.
IT'S THE JOB.

02:42.833 --> 02:44.915
YOU SURE?

02:44.915 --> 02:46.997
OF COURSE.
I'LL DO IT.

02:46.997 --> 02:48.749
UH --

02:58.679 --> 03:00.801
UH, S-SIR?
SIR, Y-YOU CAN'T PARK THERE.

03:00.801 --> 03:02.893
OH, NO, I'M NOT PARKING.
I'M JUST STOPPING FOR A SEC.

03:02.893 --> 03:03.974
NO, THIS IS
FOR PATIENTS ONLY.

03:03.974 --> 03:05.145
YEAH, YEAH, I GOT A PATIENT.
NO WORRIES.

03:07.147 --> 03:08.229
[ SIGHS ]
ALL RIGHTY.

03:09.940 --> 03:12.943
WELL, WE'RE A LITTLE LATE,
BUT WE'RE HERE.

03:12.943 --> 03:14.945
YOU READY FOR THIS?

03:14.945 --> 03:16.237
YEAH.

03:16.237 --> 03:17.818
Jackson:
DID THIS CASE A YEAR AGO.

03:17.818 --> 03:19.780
LOOKS AMAZING.

03:19.780 --> 03:21.782
AND WE'RE DOING SOMETHING
LIKE THIS AGAIN TODAY?
YEAH.

03:21.782 --> 03:25.786
APRIL'S BRINGING IN A KID FROM
JORDAN WITH OLLIER'S DISEASE.

03:25.786 --> 03:26.787
YOU CAN SEE,
THESE ARE THE ENCHONDROMAS.

03:26.787 --> 03:28.629
CARTILAGINOUS TUMORS.

03:28.629 --> 03:30.751
THEY -- THEY GROW FROM
THE GROWTH PLATES, RIGHT?
EXACTLY.

03:30.751 --> 03:32.963
WHICH IS WHY YOU'RE GONNA WANT
TO DO A WIDE LOCAL EXCISION,

03:32.963 --> 03:34.465
EXPOSE THE BONE
SO I CAN GET IN THERE

03:34.465 --> 03:35.756
AND RECONSTRUCT
THE HAND --

03:35.756 --> 03:38.549
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
I WILL?

03:38.549 --> 03:40.100
I'LL DISSECT THE TUMORS?

03:40.100 --> 03:41.762
I THOUGHT SO.

03:41.762 --> 03:43.013
IF YOU'RE UP FOR IT.

03:43.013 --> 03:45.306
[ CHUCKLES ]
HELL YES, I AM.

03:45.306 --> 03:47.648
April: ARE YOU READY?
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY UP.

03:47.648 --> 03:50.020
UH, WHY DON'T YOU HEAD UP
TO PEDS, HELP HIM GET SETTLED?

03:50.020 --> 03:51.522
YEAH.

03:55.406 --> 03:57.157
THANK YOU FOR DOING THIS.

03:57.157 --> 03:59.820
LISTEN, IT'S A GREAT CASE.
AND IT'S JUST A RESECTION.

03:59.820 --> 04:01.452
HE'S SUCH A SWEET KID.

04:01.452 --> 04:03.243
HE'S AN AMAZING KID.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.785
HE'S BEEN THROUGH HELL
IN JORDAN,

04:04.785 --> 04:07.628
AND -- AND HE JUST
NEVER GIVES UP.

04:07.628 --> 04:09.630
SINCE HE LOST HIS FAMILY, HE'S
BEEN LIVING AT THE HOSPITAL,

04:09.630 --> 04:11.211
AND WE JUST -- WE GIVE HIM
ALL THESE ODD JOBS TO DO AND --

04:11.211 --> 04:12.963
APRIL,
YOU CAN STOP SELLING HIM.

04:12.963 --> 04:14.755
OKAY? IT'S HAPPENING.

04:14.755 --> 04:16.256
WE ARE DOING IT,
SO...

04:17.588 --> 04:20.220
GOOD.
JUST -- I JUST...

04:20.220 --> 04:22.343
THANKS FOR PUTTING OUR STUFF
ASIDE, AND --

04:22.343 --> 04:24.014
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
LET'S GO SEE HIM.

04:35.105 --> 04:37.027
YES.

04:37.027 --> 04:38.899
I AM...

04:38.899 --> 04:41.161
I UNDERSTAND
I'M ON YOUR SERVICE TODAY.

04:41.161 --> 04:43.283
THAT'S RIGHT.

04:43.283 --> 04:45.536
D-DR. GREY,
I JUST WANT TO SAY,

04:45.536 --> 04:48.248
I DON'T WANT TODAY TO BE
AWKWARD OR UNCOMFORTABLE.

04:48.248 --> 04:49.540
SO DON'T MAKE IT
AWKWARD OR UNCOMFORTABLE --

04:49.540 --> 04:50.581
LIKE THIS, RIGHT NOW.

04:50.581 --> 04:52.373
[ PAGER BEEPS ]

04:52.373 --> 04:54.294
IF THERE'S ANYTHING
THAT I --

04:54.294 --> 04:56.006
CONSULT IN THE PIT.
WE'RE WALKING.

05:01.802 --> 05:04.515
ROBERT MATTHEWS, 30s,
FELL DOWN TWO FLIGHTS OF STAIRS.

05:04.515 --> 05:05.806
POSSIBLE L.O.C.

05:05.806 --> 05:07.267
HE'S BEEN COMPLAINING
OF ABDOMINAL PAIN.

05:07.267 --> 05:09.059
I CAN ARRANGE FOR A HEAD C.T.
OR PAGE NEURO.

05:09.059 --> 05:11.101
ALL I NEED
IS AN ULTRASOUND.

05:14.735 --> 05:16.196
NO!
OH!

05:16.196 --> 05:17.648
WHOA, WHOA! CALM DOWN.
OKAY.

05:17.648 --> 05:19.650
NO, I-I HAVE TO GO!

05:19.650 --> 05:21.031
OKAY.

05:21.031 --> 05:23.404
[ GRUNTING ]
RELAX!

05:23.404 --> 05:26.867
I DID SOMETHING BAD --
REALLY BAD -- AND I...

05:26.867 --> 05:27.998
WHERE AM I?

05:27.998 --> 05:29.079
HOW'D I GET HERE?

05:29.079 --> 05:30.711
RELAX.
YOU FELL DOWN SOME STAIRS.

05:30.711 --> 05:32.873
I WAS TRYING TO GET UP
TO THE CHOIR LOFT.

05:32.873 --> 05:34.545
CHOIR LOFT?

05:34.545 --> 05:36.587
I'M THE PASTOR AT FIRST
LUTHERAN, AND I HAD --

05:36.587 --> 05:37.758
THERE WAS AN ACCIDENT.

05:37.758 --> 05:39.920
I ACCIDENTALLY...

05:39.920 --> 05:41.171
OH, GOD.
I HAVE TO GO!

05:41.171 --> 05:42.262
HEY.

05:42.262 --> 05:43.844
OKAY, LISTEN, ROBERT,
YOU HAVE TO CALM DOWN,

05:43.844 --> 05:45.345
OR YOU'RE GONNA
MAKE THIS WORSE, OKAY?

05:45.345 --> 05:47.307
IT'S NOT OKAY!

05:47.307 --> 05:48.469
I SENT IT TO EVERYONE.

05:48.469 --> 05:49.770
SENT WHAT?

05:49.770 --> 05:51.732
THE CHURCH BULLETIN.

05:51.732 --> 05:54.104
I WENT TO ATTACH THE VIDEO
OF THE YOUTH VOLLEYBALL GAME,

05:54.104 --> 05:57.978
AND...I'VE BEEN
SEEING SOMEONE -- A WOMAN --

05:57.978 --> 06:00.741
A NICE, BUT...
SORT OF ADVENTUROUS WOMAN.

06:00.741 --> 06:02.573
BUT NICE AND --

06:02.573 --> 06:03.404
OKAY, NOW YOU LOST ME.

06:04.905 --> 06:06.196
I ATTACHED
THE WRONG VIDEO.

06:07.077 --> 06:07.868
[ GASPS ]

06:09.870 --> 06:12.082
YOU SENT A SEX TAPE?

06:12.082 --> 06:13.664
TO MY ENTIRE CONGREGATION.

06:13.664 --> 06:15.996
OH, GOOD GOD!

06:15.996 --> 06:19.420
YEAH, CAN WE NOT TALK
ABOUT HIM RIGHT NOW?

06:19.420 --> 06:21.882
I RODE ON A BUS,
A TRAIN, A PLANE,

06:21.882 --> 06:23.964
THREE CARS,
AND A HELICOPTER.

06:23.964 --> 06:25.506
April: THAT'S AMAZING!

06:25.506 --> 06:28.889
UM, KAMAL, I WANT YOU
TO MEET DR. AVERY.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.811
HE'S GONNA PERFORM
YOUR OPERATION.
HI.

06:30.811 --> 06:32.773
YOU ARE...THE GUY?

06:32.773 --> 06:33.974
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:33.974 --> 06:35.686
"THE GUY"?
UM...

06:35.686 --> 06:37.778
THERE SHE IS!
THE MACHINE!

06:37.778 --> 06:39.359
NATHAN!

06:39.359 --> 06:41.692
HEY. [ CHUCKLES ]
OH, MAN! HEY!

06:41.692 --> 06:44.194
THANK YOU, THANK YOU, THANK YOU
FOR BRINGING HIM HERE.

06:44.194 --> 06:45.446
HEY, COME ON.
OF COURSE.

06:45.446 --> 06:48.529
NATHAN AND I WORKED TOGETHER
ON MY LAST TOUR.

06:48.529 --> 06:51.832
DR. RIGGS, THIS IS JACKSON --
DR. AVERY.
OH.

06:51.832 --> 06:52.993
YEAH, NATHAN RIGGS.
HEY.

06:52.993 --> 06:54.294
HEY.
TRAUMA SURGEON?

06:54.294 --> 06:56.036
CARDIOTHORACIC,
BUT OVER THERE,

06:56.036 --> 06:57.878
IT'S PRETTY MUCH ALL TRAUMA,
YOU KNOW?

06:57.878 --> 07:00.000
SURE. SURE, YEAH.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.463
DR. RIGGS!
HE IS THE GUY!

07:02.463 --> 07:03.303
[ LAUGHS ]

07:03.303 --> 07:04.715
WHAT IS "THE GUY"?

07:04.715 --> 07:06.006
THE FIRST TIME
WE MET KAMAL,

07:06.006 --> 07:07.968
KEPS SAID, "I KNOW THE GUY
WHO CAN FIX YOUR HANDS,"

07:07.968 --> 07:10.180
SO EVER SINCE, HE'S BEEN TALKING
ABOUT MEETING "THE GUY."

07:10.180 --> 07:13.974
WELL, KAMAL,
LET'S TAKE A LOOK, HUH?

07:13.974 --> 07:15.726
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

07:20.901 --> 07:22.062
OHH.

07:24.404 --> 07:27.157
OKAY. LET'S GET THIS GUY
UP HERE.

07:27.157 --> 07:29.199
ALL RIGHT.
LOOK AT THIS.

07:32.162 --> 07:34.164
OKAY.

07:38.959 --> 07:40.040
UH-HUH.

07:42.923 --> 07:45.085
YOU CAN FIX THEM?

07:49.179 --> 07:50.220
THAT'S THE PLAN.

07:54.394 --> 07:56.016
YOU NEVER TOLD ME
IT WAS THIS ADVANCED.

07:56.016 --> 07:57.938
THE TUMORS
ARE MASSIVE.

07:57.938 --> 07:59.149
OKAY, MAYBE I DOWNPLAYED IT
A LITTLE.

07:59.149 --> 08:00.651
YOU DOWNPLAYED IT?!
THIS LOOKS IMPOSSIBLE!

08:00.651 --> 08:02.813
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
YOU SENT HIM THE SCANS, RIGHT?

08:02.813 --> 08:04.154
DIDN'T YOU SEE
THE SCANS?

08:05.445 --> 08:08.238
SHE TOLD ME
THE SCANS WERE LOST IN JORDAN.

08:08.238 --> 08:09.319
I DIDN'T WANT HIM
TO SEE THE SCANS.

08:09.319 --> 08:10.320
WAIT. WHAT?

08:10.320 --> 08:11.532
KEPS, WHAT THE HELL?!

08:11.532 --> 08:12.993
YOU LIED!

08:12.993 --> 08:14.535
IF YOU HAD SEEN THE SCANS,
YOU MIGHT HAVE SAID NO,

08:14.535 --> 08:17.327
AND I WANTED YOU
TO MEET THAT LITTLE BOY.

08:17.327 --> 08:18.709
AND HE'S HERE NOW.

08:18.709 --> 08:20.120
SO HOW DO WE HELP HIM?

08:34.394 --> 08:35.806
HEY. SO, BLAKE'S
ON MEREDITH'S SERVICE?

08:35.806 --> 08:36.847
UH, LOOKS LIKE IT.

08:36.847 --> 08:38.228
SHE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT?
I DON'T KNOW.

08:38.228 --> 08:39.439
WE HAVEN'T SPOKEN
SINCE THE PARTY.

08:39.439 --> 08:40.641
SHE FEELS LIKE
I'M ON MEREDITH'S SIDE.

08:40.641 --> 08:41.942
AND I AM, YOU KNOW?

08:41.942 --> 08:43.523
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
I'M NOT ON PENNY'S SIDE, TOO.

08:43.523 --> 08:46.276
AND NOW MEREDITH'S NOT EVEN
TALKING TO ME, SO WIN-WIN!

08:46.276 --> 08:47.447
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

08:47.447 --> 08:48.989
OH, GOD.

08:48.989 --> 08:51.031
78 NEW MESSAGES?

08:51.031 --> 08:52.032
[ GRUNTS ]

08:52.032 --> 08:54.955
THEY KNOW.

08:54.955 --> 08:56.536
THEY ALL KNOW.

08:58.709 --> 09:00.751
WHAT'S
YOUR ASSESSMENT?

09:00.751 --> 09:02.042
WELL, I THINK --
NOT YOU -- BLAKE.

09:03.463 --> 09:05.255
ULTRASOUND SHOWED FLUID
IN MORISON'S POUCH.

09:05.255 --> 09:06.546
WE SHOULD GET
AN ABDOMINAL C.T.

09:06.546 --> 09:08.759
AND WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR
ON THE C.T.?

09:08.759 --> 09:11.011
WE NEED TO RULE OUT BLEEDING
FROM THE LIVER OR THE SPLEEN.

09:11.011 --> 09:12.673
WE SHOULD ALSO EVALUATE
THE RETROPERITONEAL SPACE.

09:12.673 --> 09:14.224
IF THERE'S ACTIVE BLEEDING
ON THE C.T.,

09:14.224 --> 09:15.936
WE SET HIM UP
FOR AN EX-LAP.

09:15.936 --> 09:17.267
ARE YOU FORGETTING
ANYTHING?

09:17.267 --> 09:19.730
UH, WE CLEARED
HIS C-SPINE,

09:19.730 --> 09:22.232
WE SENT BLOOD OUT
FOR A TRAUMA PANEL, TOX SCREEN,

09:22.232 --> 09:24.354
ALCOHOL LEVELS.

09:24.354 --> 09:26.486
AND?

09:26.486 --> 09:27.648
AND, UH...

09:27.648 --> 09:28.779
ORDER A TYPE
AND CROSSMATCH.

09:28.779 --> 09:31.241
OH. OF COURSE.

09:31.241 --> 09:33.363
OBVIOUSLY.
I-I SKIPPED THAT.

09:33.363 --> 09:34.905
OKAY, WELL,
LET'S NOT SKIP STEPS.

09:34.905 --> 09:36.617
WE'RE A LEVEL I
TRAUMA CENTER.

09:36.617 --> 09:38.288
I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT DILLARD TAUGHT YOU.

09:38.288 --> 09:41.501
LET'S FILL HIM WITH FLUIDS
AND PREP HIM FOR A C.T.

09:41.501 --> 09:44.875
[ CURTAIN RATTLES ]

09:44.875 --> 09:46.206
I DIDN'T LIE.
I --

09:46.206 --> 09:47.708
YOU BENT THE TRUTH
A BIT.

09:47.708 --> 09:49.509
UNTIL IT BROKE.

09:49.509 --> 09:51.471
IT WAS A GOOD LIE.
[ SCOFFS ]

09:51.471 --> 09:53.423
OKAY, IT WAS A BAD LIE,
BUT FOR A GOOD REASON.

09:53.423 --> 09:55.305
YOU KNOW, YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
SAYING YES TO ANYTHING LATELY --

09:55.305 --> 09:56.386
NOT WHEN IT COMES
FROM ME.

09:56.386 --> 09:58.348
LOOK AT THE SCANS,
APRIL.

09:58.348 --> 10:01.141
OKAY, THESE AREAS ARE
PURE CARTILAGE, RIGHT?

10:01.141 --> 10:02.983
THEY PROBABLY DESTROYED ANY BONE
THAT WAS IN THEIR PATH.

10:02.983 --> 10:04.524
GUYS,
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW

10:04.524 --> 10:06.647
THERE'S ANYTHING RESEMBLING
HANDS UNDERNEATH THESE THINGS.

10:06.647 --> 10:08.148
CAN YOU EVEN REPAIR THE TENDONS
AND THE NEUROVASCULAR BUNDLES?

10:08.148 --> 10:09.399
THAT'S DOUBTFUL.

10:09.399 --> 10:11.571
WELL, HOPKINS AND CASE WESTERN
DID SIMILAR CASES.

10:11.571 --> 10:13.073
THEY -- THEY RECONSTRUCTED
USING BONE GRAFTS.

10:13.073 --> 10:14.364
OH, SO HAVE I,
AND YOU KNOW THOSE CASES

10:14.364 --> 10:15.615
ARE NOTHING
COMPARED TO KAMAL'S.

10:15.615 --> 10:17.157
APRIL,
HE'S SAYING NO.

10:17.157 --> 10:19.499
[ SIGHS ]
LOOK, WE'LL JUST KEEP LOOKING
UNTIL WE FIND SOMEONE.

10:19.499 --> 10:22.162
AND THEY WILL ALL SAY
THE EXACT SAME THING.

10:23.583 --> 10:25.005
THANKS.

10:25.005 --> 10:26.837
THANKS
FOR TAKING THE TIME.

10:29.670 --> 10:31.091
LOOK,
I'M NOT SAYING NO.

10:31.091 --> 10:34.755
I'M SAYING I...
WILL DO SOME BIOPSIES

10:34.755 --> 10:36.677
SO THAT WE CAN ALL
GET A FULL PICTURE

10:36.677 --> 10:38.468
OF WHAT IT IS
WE'RE DEALING WITH HERE.

10:38.468 --> 10:39.680
[ SIGHS ]

10:39.680 --> 10:40.640
THANK YOU.

10:40.640 --> 10:41.722
[ SIGHS ]

10:44.474 --> 10:48.358
I HEARD THERE WAS A BAD DRIVER
IN THE HOUSE.

10:48.358 --> 10:49.730
[ Chuckling ]
UNCLE RICHARD!

10:49.730 --> 10:52.402
[ LAUGHTER ]

10:52.402 --> 10:55.535
MAN, YOU LOOK...BALD.

10:55.535 --> 10:57.197
[ CHUCKLES ]
AND YOU LOOK OLD.

10:57.197 --> 10:58.488
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

10:58.488 --> 11:00.120
"UNCLE RICHARD"?

11:00.120 --> 11:03.083
YEAH, ADELE AND I KNEW PAUL
AND HIS LATE WIFE, LOIS,

11:03.083 --> 11:04.164
BEFORE
WE GOT MARRIED.

11:04.164 --> 11:05.625
BUMPY AND I
GO WAY BACK.

11:05.625 --> 11:07.748
"BUMPY"?
WHY "BUMPY"?

11:07.748 --> 11:09.790
UH...HEY.

11:09.790 --> 11:10.590
MORNING, ANGELA.

11:10.590 --> 11:11.712
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:11.712 --> 11:13.173
UH...

11:13.173 --> 11:14.885
TELL ME
ABOUT THE ACCIDENT.

11:14.885 --> 11:16.386
HOW DID IT HAPPEN?

11:16.386 --> 11:18.008
ALL I KNOW IS
I PRESSED THE BRAKE,

11:18.008 --> 11:19.720
BUT THE DAMN CAR
KEPT GOING.

11:19.720 --> 11:20.600
RIGHT INTO A TREE.

11:20.600 --> 11:22.352
[ GASPS ]

11:22.352 --> 11:25.065
YEAH, SHE'S GOT A SEVERELY
DISPLACED CLAVICULAR FRACTURE

11:25.065 --> 11:27.898
AND A WEAK PULSE
IN HER RIGHT ARM.

11:27.898 --> 11:29.569
HOW ABOUT PAUL?

11:29.569 --> 11:31.401
I'LL BE FINE.
ANGELA GOT THE WORST OF IT.

11:31.401 --> 11:33.273
STILL, I WANT TO WORK YOU UP,
TOO, JUST TO BE SAFE.

11:33.273 --> 11:35.405
SO I'LL GO AHEAD
AND SCHEDULE THAT C.T.A.

11:35.405 --> 11:37.157
THAT SOUND GOOD TO YOU,
BUMPY?

11:37.157 --> 11:38.869
THAT'LL BE
QUITE ENOUGH OF THAT.

11:38.869 --> 11:40.240
SORRY.

11:40.240 --> 11:41.782
DR. BUMPY.

11:41.782 --> 11:43.323
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

11:49.329 --> 11:51.381
TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE.

11:51.381 --> 11:53.003
RETROPERITONEAL FLUID.

11:53.003 --> 11:55.095
AROUND WHAT?
BE SPECIFIC.

11:59.099 --> 12:00.761
THE RIGHT KIDNEY.

12:00.761 --> 12:04.224
IT'S A GRADE IV INJURY
WITH AN ACTIVE EXTRAVASATION.

12:04.224 --> 12:07.017
WE ARE GONNA NEED TO DO
AN EX-LAP.

12:07.017 --> 12:08.809
SHOULD I CALL UPSTAIRS?

12:08.809 --> 12:11.351
WHAT DO WE HAVE?

12:11.351 --> 12:14.614
UH, PATIENT CAME IN
WITH A HEAD LAC, G.C.S. OF 14,

12:14.614 --> 12:15.906
LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS
AT THE SCENE --

12:15.906 --> 12:17.237
CAN YOU CLEAR
THE HEAD C.T.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.239
SO WE CAN TAKE HIM UP
FOR AN EX-LAP?

12:19.239 --> 12:22.322
THERE'S NO SHIFT,
CONTUSION, OR BLEED.

12:22.322 --> 12:23.824
IT'S A MILD CONCUSSION.

12:23.824 --> 12:26.536
I'LL DO A QUICK EXAM,
BUT HE'S CLEARED FOR SURGERY.

12:26.536 --> 12:28.919
IS THIS THE PASTOR
WHO GAVE HIS CONGREGATION

12:28.919 --> 12:30.831
A, UH...
SPECIAL BLESSING?

12:30.831 --> 12:32.793
WORD TRAVELS FAST.

12:32.793 --> 12:34.294
ALL AROUND THE HOSPITAL.

12:34.294 --> 12:36.636
YEAH, I BET THE PEWS
WILL BE FULL ON SUNDAY.

12:41.381 --> 12:43.934
MONITOR
FOR ANY NEURO DEFICITS.

12:43.934 --> 12:46.346
I WILL DO ANOTHER CHECK,
POST-OP.

12:46.346 --> 12:48.098
BLAKE, GET HIM READY
FOR TRANSPORT.

12:48.098 --> 12:49.599
EDWARDS,
SHOW HER WHERE IT IS.

13:01.571 --> 13:04.284
IT'S NOT ENOUGH TO HAVE HER HERE
IN THE SAME BUILDING.

13:04.284 --> 13:06.036
YOU INVITED HER
ON YOUR SERVICE, TOO?

13:06.036 --> 13:08.248
I AM TRYING
TO RISE ABOVE.

13:08.248 --> 13:10.170
AND YOU SHOULD, TOO.

13:10.170 --> 13:13.543
NO, YOU SHOULD HAVE ENDED IT
THAT NIGHT.

13:13.543 --> 13:15.465
[ SIGHS ]

13:15.465 --> 13:17.177
FORGET IT.

13:17.177 --> 13:19.219
IT WAS BETTER
WHEN WE WEREN'T TALKING.

13:24.764 --> 13:27.727
AS I FEARED, THE BIOPSY SHOWED
PRECANCEROUS CELLS IN THE TUMOR.

13:27.727 --> 13:29.269
BOTH SIDES.

13:29.269 --> 13:30.480
[ SIGHS ]

13:30.480 --> 13:32.352
OKAY. THEN WE NEED
TO GET IN THERE A.S.A.P. --

13:32.352 --> 13:35.275
APRIL, LISTEN, THERE
IS NO CLEAR WAY TO
EXCISE ALL THE TUMOR.

13:35.275 --> 13:39.399
SO I HAVE TO RECOMMEND...
AMPUTATION.

13:39.399 --> 13:40.861
OF BOTH HANDS.

13:40.861 --> 13:42.532
NO.

13:42.532 --> 13:44.494
IT IS HIS BEST SHOT
BEFORE IT PROGRESSES TO CANCER.

13:44.494 --> 13:47.157
NO. I BROUGHT HIM TO YOU
TO SAVE HIS HANDS.

13:47.157 --> 13:48.748
THIS IS HOW
WE SAVE HIS LIFE.

13:48.748 --> 13:50.370
WELL, I DON'T KNOW.

13:50.370 --> 13:51.831
I DON'T SEE
HOW HE SURVIVES OVER THERE

13:51.831 --> 13:53.543
WITH NO HANDS AND NO ONE
TO TAKE CARE OF HIM.

13:53.543 --> 13:55.545
I UNDERSTAND.
I'M SORRY.

13:55.545 --> 13:57.457
I COULD HAVE TOLD YOU SOONER
IF I HAD ALL THE INFORMATION.

13:57.457 --> 13:58.628
YOU MEAN YOU COULD HAVE
GIVEN UP SOONER.

13:58.628 --> 14:00.720
YES, YOU'RE RIGHT -- BECAUSE
THERE'S NOTHING TO BE DONE.

14:00.720 --> 14:01.801
YOU COULD TRY!

14:01.801 --> 14:03.223
YOU COULD MAKE AN EFFORT

14:03.223 --> 14:05.175
INSTEAD OF JUST GIVING UP
AND WALKING AWAY!

14:05.175 --> 14:06.386
AND YOU DON'T THINK
I WANT TO?

14:06.386 --> 14:07.677
ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE NOT DOING THIS.

14:07.677 --> 14:09.309
COULD YOU LEAVE US ALONE
FOR A SECOND, PLEASE?

14:09.309 --> 14:10.520
OH, ABSOLUTELY,
I'M GONNA LEAVE,

14:10.520 --> 14:12.812
AND I'M GONNA TAKE KAMAL
WITH ME, ALL RIGHT?

14:12.812 --> 14:15.185
'CAUSE THIS ISN'T
ABOUT YOU TWO! OKAY?

14:15.185 --> 14:18.318
THIS IS ABOUT A LITTLE BOY WHO
HAD TO SEE HIS FAMILY MURDERED,

14:18.318 --> 14:19.689
WHO SAW HIS HOME
BURNT TO THE GROUND,

14:19.689 --> 14:21.281
WHO WOULD'VE BEEN TAKEN
AS A CHILD SOLDIER

14:21.281 --> 14:23.243
IF IT WASN'T
FOR HIS DEFORMED HANDS.

14:23.243 --> 14:24.864
ALL RIGHT,
HE DOESN'T HAVE THE TIME

14:24.864 --> 14:27.247
FOR YOU GUYS
TO BE WORKING OUT YOUR CRAP!

14:27.247 --> 14:29.119
HE DESERVES
THE BEST CARE HE CAN GET,

14:29.119 --> 14:30.490
AND I'M GONNA MAKE SURE
HE FINDS IT.

14:32.202 --> 14:34.754
WHY'D YOU EVEN
BRING HIM TO ME?

14:34.754 --> 14:36.796
YOU SAW THE SCANS.
YOU'RE A GOOD SURGEON.

14:36.796 --> 14:37.797
YOU KNEW
THIS WAS HOPELESS.

14:37.797 --> 14:39.499
I WASN'T HOPELESS.

14:39.499 --> 14:41.421
I DON'T KNOW
WHY YOU ARE.

14:41.421 --> 14:44.134
BECAUSE THERE'S NOTHING HERE
TO SAVE.

14:45.305 --> 14:46.716
[ SIGHS ]

14:53.513 --> 14:56.726
WHAT'S THE TRICKIEST PART
OF A PARTIAL NEPHRECTOMY?

14:56.726 --> 14:59.149
WELL, I THINK
IT'S ESSENTIAL THAT --
NOT YOU -- BLAKE.

14:59.149 --> 15:00.610
MOBILIZING THE COLON
QUICKLY

15:00.610 --> 15:01.942
TO GET ADEQUATE EXPOSURE
OF THE KIDNEY.

15:01.942 --> 15:03.363
BY YOUR THIRD YEAR,

15:03.363 --> 15:04.524
YOU SHOULD KNOW THIS SURGERY
INSIDE AND OUT.

15:04.524 --> 15:05.825
I DO.
OKAY.

15:05.825 --> 15:07.617
SO YOU ARE GONNA
WALK ME THROUGH THIS.

15:07.617 --> 15:08.788
YOUR HANDS ARE MY HANDS,

15:08.788 --> 15:10.530
AND MY HANDS DO NOT LIKE
MAKING MISTAKES.

15:10.530 --> 15:11.831
ARE YOU READY?

15:11.831 --> 15:13.453
I AM.
YES, I'M READY.

15:13.453 --> 15:14.995
WITH WHAT? BECAUSE I HAVE
NOTHING IN MY HANDS.

15:14.995 --> 15:16.086
RIGHT.
UH, 10 BLADE.

15:16.086 --> 15:18.168
10 BLADE.

15:19.799 --> 15:22.092
Maggie: C.T.A. RESULTS
SHOWED AN INJURY

15:22.092 --> 15:23.883
TO AN ARTERY
IN ANGELA'S CHEST.

15:23.883 --> 15:25.715
SHE'S ON HER WAY
TO PRE-OP NOW.

15:25.715 --> 15:28.258
SHE DOESN'T WANT YOU TO WORRY,
AND NEITHER DO I.

15:28.258 --> 15:30.390
[ SIGHS ]
YOU SOUND JUST LIKE BUMPY.

15:30.390 --> 15:33.353
YOU HAVE TO TELL ME
WHY YOU CALL HIM "BUMPY."

15:33.353 --> 15:35.765
[ LAUGHS ]
WELL, THAT'S 'CAUSE,

15:35.765 --> 15:37.607
BACK IN THE DAY,
WHEN WE WERE IN COLLEGE --

15:37.607 --> 15:40.060
GOT YOUR RESULTS BACK.

15:40.060 --> 15:41.651
OH,
YOU HURT YOUR FOOT?

15:41.651 --> 15:42.652
NO, NO, IT'S FINE.

15:42.652 --> 15:45.445
IT'S...PINS AND NEEDLES,
IS ALL.

15:45.445 --> 15:47.777
IT'S -- IT'S, UH...
IT'S JUST A LITTLE NUMB.

15:47.777 --> 15:49.029
IT'LL GO AWAY.

15:49.029 --> 15:52.282
I DON'T THINK IT WILL --
NOT BY ITSELF.

15:52.282 --> 15:55.875
YOUR LABS SHOW
ELEVATED HEMOGLOBIN A1c LEVELS.

15:55.875 --> 15:58.038
AND YOUR BLOOD GLUCOSE LEVEL
IS VERY HIGH.

15:58.038 --> 15:59.339
YOU'RE DIABETIC.

15:59.339 --> 16:01.841
BUT YOU ALREADY KNEW THAT.

16:01.841 --> 16:05.465
LISTEN, BUMPY, I'VE BEEN TAKING
BETTER CARE OF MYSELF.

16:05.465 --> 16:07.347
ANGELA DOESN'T KNOW,
AND -- AND I WANT US
TO KEEP IT THAT WAY.

16:07.347 --> 16:08.798
THAT PAIN IN YOUR FOOT?

16:08.798 --> 16:10.470
IT'S A SYMPTOM, PAUL.

16:10.470 --> 16:12.262
IT'S CALLED
DIABETIC NERVE PAIN.

16:12.262 --> 16:14.974
IT COULD BE THE REASON
YOU CRASHED YOUR CAR.

16:16.556 --> 16:18.808
ARE YOU SAYING
I PUT MY BABY IN THE HOSPITAL?

16:18.808 --> 16:20.940
NO.
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

16:20.940 --> 16:22.562
SHE LOVES YOU.
SHE'LL UNDERSTAND.

16:22.562 --> 16:23.773
JUST TELL HER --

16:23.773 --> 16:25.105
DO YOU HAVE ANY CHILDREN,
RICHARD?

16:29.159 --> 16:31.371
DO YOU?

16:31.371 --> 16:32.822
NO. NO, I DON'T.

16:32.822 --> 16:35.705
SO YOU DON'T KNOW A DAMN THING.
YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY UNDERSTAND.

16:35.705 --> 16:37.827
PLEASE, JUST --

16:37.827 --> 16:40.500
JUST TAKE CARE OF
MY LITTLE GIRL, AND LEAVE ME BE.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.253
I'LL LET YOU KNOW AS SOON
AS ANGELA'S OUT OF SURGERY.

16:53.223 --> 16:55.475
AND NOW
JACKSON WANTS TO AMPUTATE.

16:55.475 --> 16:58.058
HE WON'T EVEN TRY.
HE SAID IT WAS HOPELESS.

16:58.058 --> 17:00.900
HE -- HE ASKED ME WHY I EVEN
BROUGHT KAMAL TO HIM.

17:00.900 --> 17:01.981
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:01.981 --> 17:02.902
WHAT?

17:02.902 --> 17:05.065
WELL? WHY DID YOU?

17:05.065 --> 17:07.857
I MEAN, THE SCANS WERE SO BAD,
YOU HAD TO LIE ABOUT THEM.

17:07.857 --> 17:10.910
YOU LIED
ABOUT A LITTLE BOY, APRIL.

17:10.910 --> 17:13.283
I'M S-- WHAT --
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

17:13.283 --> 17:15.705
[ SIGHS ]

17:15.705 --> 17:17.417
NOTHING. SORRY.

17:17.417 --> 17:19.079
W--

17:21.040 --> 17:22.752
I'M SAYING,
I KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE

17:22.752 --> 17:24.624
WHEN IT FEELS LIKE
EVERYTHING'S COMING APART

17:24.624 --> 17:28.548
AND YOU NEED SOMETHING
TO PULL IT TOGETHER.

17:28.548 --> 17:30.090
I JUST...

17:31.971 --> 17:33.052
I KNOW.

17:36.976 --> 17:39.309
ARE YOU SURE?

17:39.309 --> 17:42.522
WELL, MAYBE YOU CAN SHOW THEM
TO ROGERS.

17:42.522 --> 17:44.444
YEAH,
I'D APPRECIATE IT.

17:44.444 --> 17:46.566
ALL RIGHT, CALL ME BACK.
THANKS, CHARLIE.

17:48.488 --> 17:49.689
RIGGS?

17:54.364 --> 17:55.955
HUNT.

17:55.955 --> 17:57.747
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

17:57.747 --> 17:59.699
APRIL KEPNER AND I
MET IN JORDAN.

17:59.699 --> 18:01.291
I'VE BEEN WORKING WITH THE
RELIEF EFFORT IN AFGHANISTAN --

18:01.291 --> 18:03.463
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

18:03.463 --> 18:05.375
WE HAVE A PATIENT
WITH OLLIER'S DISEASE.

18:05.375 --> 18:06.836
BROUGHT HIM IN
TO YOUR HAND GUY.

18:06.836 --> 18:08.338
AND THEN YOU'RE LEAVING.

18:08.338 --> 18:09.709
YEAH, WELL, MAYBE
A LITTLE SOONER THAN I --

18:09.709 --> 18:12.051
I'M NOT ASKING YOU, RIGGS.
I'M TELLING YOU.

18:14.714 --> 18:16.176
NICE CATCHING UP.

18:18.348 --> 18:19.719
INCISE GEROTA'S FASCIA.

18:19.719 --> 18:22.101
NOW IDENTIFY AND DEBRIDE
DEVITALIZED TISSUE.

18:22.101 --> 18:23.313
GO ON.

18:23.313 --> 18:26.486
U-UM...
CAUTERIZE CORTICAL BLEEDERS

18:26.486 --> 18:29.108
AND ESTABLISH HEMOSTASIS
BEFORE CLOSURE.

18:29.108 --> 18:31.191
NOW CLOSE USING
A RUNNING ABSORBABLE SUTURE

18:31.191 --> 18:32.822
TO AVOID
POST-OP FISTULAS.

18:32.822 --> 18:35.195
YOU CAN EVEN REINFORCE
USING AN ABSORBABLE MESH.

18:35.195 --> 18:37.867
WELL, THAT'S THINKING AHEAD.
I LIKE THAT.

18:37.867 --> 18:39.449
DR. GREY. DR. BLAKE.

18:39.449 --> 18:42.001
I THOUGHT I'D STOP IN TO SEE
HOW THE FIRST DAY WAS GOING.

18:42.001 --> 18:44.294
THANK YOU, SIR.
IT'S BEEN --

18:44.294 --> 18:46.506
BLAKE HAS BEEN DICTATING
MY SURGICAL STEPS.

18:46.506 --> 18:48.798
GREAT. HOW'S SHE DOING?
NOT TOO WELL.

18:48.798 --> 18:50.670
IF I HAD DONE
WHAT SHE JUST SUGGESTED,

18:50.670 --> 18:53.713
THE PATIENT WOULD HAVE
MAJOR RENAL CORTEX BLEEDING.

18:53.713 --> 18:54.924
WHAT DID YOU MISS?

18:54.924 --> 18:57.177
I -- WHAT?

18:57.177 --> 19:00.390
WHAT DID I DO
THAT YOU MISSED?

19:00.390 --> 19:02.892
UH, DEBRIDE,
HEMOSTASIS, CLOSE...

19:02.892 --> 19:04.644
COME ON.
FIGURE IT OUT.

19:04.644 --> 19:07.106
I WAS WATCHING YOU.
I DIDN'T SEE.

19:07.106 --> 19:09.189
DeLUCA,
CAN YOU FILL IN THE BLANKS?

19:09.189 --> 19:13.032
UM, DR. BLAKE DIDN'T TELL YOU
TO CLAMP THE HILUM.

19:13.032 --> 19:14.824
DR. GREY,
THE HILUM IS CLAMPED.

19:14.824 --> 19:17.367
IT IS, SIR,
BECAUSE I CLAMPED IT ON MY OWN.

19:17.367 --> 19:19.369
I DIDN'T SKIP A STEP,
AND THEREFORE,

19:19.369 --> 19:21.491
THE PATIENT DID NOT HEMORRHAGE
AND DIE.

19:21.491 --> 19:23.703
BLAKE, HAND YOUR SUCTION
TO DeLUCA.

19:23.703 --> 19:25.835
DR. GREY,
I KNOW THIS PROCEDURE.

19:25.835 --> 19:27.627
YOU WOULD'VE KILLED
THE PATIENT, BLAKE.

19:27.627 --> 19:30.089
IF YOUR HANDS HAD BEEN
MY HANDS ON THIS PATIENT,

19:30.089 --> 19:31.381
HE'D BE DEAD.

19:31.381 --> 19:32.382
IT'S THAT SIMPLE.

19:32.382 --> 19:33.343
STEP AWAY FROM THE TABLE.

19:39.469 --> 19:40.640
[ SUCTION ]

19:57.657 --> 19:58.988
WHAT'S WRONG?

19:58.988 --> 20:00.320
DR. GREY
IS WHAT'S WRONG.

20:01.621 --> 20:02.782
I'M NEW.

20:02.782 --> 20:04.624
AND ATTENDINGS ARE HARD
ON RESIDENTS.

20:04.624 --> 20:06.416
I KNOW THAT.
IT'S HOW WE LEARN.

20:06.416 --> 20:09.088
AND SHE SHOULD BE HARD ON ME.
SHE SHOULD BE GRILLING ME.

20:09.088 --> 20:12.171
AND I SHOULD BE ABLE
TO HANDLE IT.

20:12.171 --> 20:15.004
BUT I LET HER IN MY HEAD.
I FROZE.

20:15.004 --> 20:17.837
I KNEW THAT SURGERY
BACKWARDS AND FORWARDS.

20:17.837 --> 20:19.098
OKAY,
I CAN TALK TO HER.

20:19.098 --> 20:20.840
NO. DON'T.

20:20.840 --> 20:23.473
I'M SORRY.
I JUST...

20:23.473 --> 20:25.845
I WILL FIGURE THIS OUT.

20:25.845 --> 20:27.727
IT'S NOT YOUR PROBLEM.

20:37.487 --> 20:41.160
I SENT THE BIOPSIES, THE SCANS
TO THREE OTHER GUYS.

20:41.160 --> 20:42.572
ANY LUCK?

20:42.572 --> 20:43.863
NO.

20:43.863 --> 20:45.745
WELL, I'D LIKE
TO HAVE BEEN WRONG.

20:48.167 --> 20:50.460
HEY, LOOK, I'M SORRY
YOU GOT PULLED INTO THIS, MAN.

20:50.460 --> 20:51.501
APRIL CAN BE --

20:51.501 --> 20:53.423
NO, LOOK, I KNOW.

20:53.423 --> 20:54.874
SHE'S THE MACHINE.

20:54.874 --> 20:57.547
SHE'S THE...WHAT?

20:57.547 --> 21:00.470
OH, THAT'S WHAT WE CALL HER
OVER THERE -- "THE MACHINE."

21:00.470 --> 21:02.592
IT NEVER SLOWS DOWN,
NEVER LETS IT GET TO HER.

21:02.592 --> 21:04.884
JUST MAKES EVERYONE ELSE
WANT TO WORK HARDER.

21:04.884 --> 21:08.938
WHEN SHE DECIDES ON SOMETHING,
NOTHING'S GONNA STOP HER.

21:08.938 --> 21:11.851
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU CAN'T CALL THAT ONE OFF.

21:11.851 --> 21:13.853
NO, THAT'S TRUE.

21:13.853 --> 21:16.195
THING IS,
SHE'S USUALLY RIGHT.

21:24.534 --> 21:27.246
GO FIND OUT WHAT CALLIE TORRES
IS DOING RIGHT NOW.

21:34.834 --> 21:36.916
OH. ANGELA'S SURGERY
IS OVER?

21:36.916 --> 21:38.758
HOW -- HOW'D IT GO?

21:38.758 --> 21:40.880
DID A PRIMARY REPAIR
OF THE SUBCLAVIAN ARTERY.

21:40.880 --> 21:42.131
IT WENT VERY WELL.

21:42.131 --> 21:43.513
YOU CAN TELL YOUR FRIEND
SHE'S FINE.

21:43.513 --> 21:44.634
MAGGIE, UH...

21:44.634 --> 21:46.636
ABOUT PAUL --

21:46.636 --> 21:49.268
YOU KNOW, WHAT HE SAID
ABOUT MY NOT HAVING CHILDREN...

21:49.268 --> 21:51.020
PAUL KNEW ME WITH ADELE,
MY WIFE --

21:51.020 --> 21:54.063
I KNOW. I KNOW.
IT'S -- IT'S AWKWARD. AWFUL.

21:54.063 --> 21:55.855
NO, YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY
ANOTHER WORD. I GET IT.

21:55.855 --> 21:57.106
OKAY.

21:57.106 --> 21:58.858
I JUST WANTED
TO MAKE SURE --

21:58.858 --> 22:02.281
DON'T...
SAY ANOTHER WORD.

22:03.943 --> 22:05.745
ARE Y-YOU --

22:05.745 --> 22:08.157
NO. NO, NO. OF COURSE NOT.
THIS IS, UM, THIS IS ALLERGIES.

22:08.157 --> 22:09.449
ALLERGIES?

22:09.449 --> 22:11.451
CAN WE PLEASE PRETEND
THAT IT'S ALLERGIES?

22:11.451 --> 22:13.082
MAGGIE,
IF I DID SOMETHING --

22:13.082 --> 22:14.794
NO, NO. GOD, NO.

22:14.794 --> 22:16.416
YOU -- YOU CHEATED
ON YOUR WIFE.

22:16.416 --> 22:19.549
WHY SHOULD YOU ADMIT THAT
TO YOUR FRIEND?

22:19.549 --> 22:21.340
WHO WOULD THAT HELP?

22:21.340 --> 22:24.263
NOT YOU, NOT HIM.

22:24.263 --> 22:25.925
AND, YOU KNOW,
YOU DON'T OWE ME ANYTHING.

22:25.925 --> 22:27.056
YOU AND I,
WE'RE NOT --

22:27.056 --> 22:29.228
I DON'T KNOW WHAT WE ARE.

22:29.228 --> 22:30.600
THAT'S JUST THE THING.

22:30.600 --> 22:32.932
I DON'T EXACTLY KNOW
HOW TO A-ADDRESS YOU --

22:32.932 --> 22:34.023
YEAH, YOU DON'T HAVE TO.
BUT --

22:34.023 --> 22:35.935
IT'S FINE.

22:35.935 --> 22:38.608
YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF -- REALLY.

22:38.608 --> 22:39.609
BUT --

22:43.943 --> 22:46.746
[ Voice breaking ]
SO, THEY WOULD JUST BE GONE?

22:46.746 --> 22:48.287
BOTH OF THEM?

22:50.119 --> 22:51.951
WE WOULD HAVE TO
AMPUTATE THEM

22:51.951 --> 22:55.044
RIGHT -- RIGHT ABOUT HERE,
AT THE WRIST.

22:55.044 --> 22:57.206
YOU SEE?

22:57.206 --> 22:59.048
ON BOTH SIDES.

23:01.090 --> 23:03.172
WILL I STILL
CARRY THINGS?

23:05.344 --> 23:06.426
WELL, LET'S TALK
ABOUT THAT, BUDDY.

23:13.773 --> 23:15.605
YOU'LL BE HERE
WHEN I'M DONE?

23:15.605 --> 23:17.817
[ SIGHS ]
YES. I PROMISE.

23:17.817 --> 23:19.859
YOU SURE ABOUT THIS?

23:19.859 --> 23:22.071
NOPE.
NOT EVEN A LITTLE BIT.

23:22.071 --> 23:24.193
WE'LL HAVE A SODA
WAITING FOR YOU, OKAY?

23:27.947 --> 23:29.158
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

23:29.158 --> 23:30.620
OKAY.

23:32.952 --> 23:34.203
GOD.

23:35.455 --> 23:37.126
ALL RIGHT, GUYS,
HOW WE DOING THIS?

23:37.126 --> 23:38.337
DOING WHAT?

23:38.337 --> 23:39.799
I FIGURE
WE'LL JUST DEBULK THE TUMOR

23:39.799 --> 23:41.300
FROM THE DORSAL SURFACE,
AND YOU CAN SHOW ME

23:41.300 --> 23:43.543
WHAT, IF ANY,
USABLE BONE WE CAN FIND.

23:43.543 --> 23:45.214
THERE'S BEEN
A CHANGE OF PLANS.

23:45.214 --> 23:46.425
YEAH,
JUDGING BY THE SCANS,

23:46.425 --> 23:48.678
I'M NOT SURE
THERE'S ANYTHING AT ALL.
I KNOW.

23:48.678 --> 23:51.050
IT JUST MIGHT END UP BEING
THE WORLD'S SLOWEST AMPUTATION,

23:51.050 --> 23:53.432
BUT...
CAN'T HURT TO TRY.

23:53.432 --> 23:54.814
MM-HMM.

23:56.686 --> 23:58.608
BUT...YOU TOLD KAMAL
THAT HE WOULDN'T --

23:58.608 --> 24:00.019
WE LIED.

24:01.731 --> 24:04.023
WE HAD TO. DIDN'T WANT
TO GET HIS HOPES UP AGAIN.

24:04.023 --> 24:05.274
HE'S GONNA TRY?

24:05.274 --> 24:06.826
MM-HMM.

24:08.447 --> 24:10.490
YOU LIED! TO ME!

24:10.490 --> 24:12.872
IT WAS A GOOD LIE.
COME ON. IT WAS A GOOD LIE.

24:12.872 --> 24:13.873
[ LAUGHS ]

24:13.873 --> 24:16.035
OH, MY GOD.

24:17.707 --> 24:19.458
HE'S GONNA TRY.

24:22.341 --> 24:23.963
WE NEED TO TALK.

24:23.963 --> 24:25.675
WHAT'S WRONG?

24:25.675 --> 24:28.257
I THOUGHT YOU WERE STEPPING UP,
PUTTING BLAKE ON YOUR SERVICE,

24:28.257 --> 24:30.850
BUT WHAT I SAW IN THAT O.R.
WASN'T TEACHING.

24:30.850 --> 24:32.762
SHE CRAPPED OUT
ON A BASIC SURGICAL PRINCIPLE.

24:32.762 --> 24:34.804
YOU WERE HAZING HER.

24:34.804 --> 24:37.687
IF SHE CRACKS UNDER THE PRESSURE
OF AN EMERGENT SURGERY,

24:37.687 --> 24:39.809
SHE DOES NOT BELONG
IN THIS PROGRAM.

24:39.809 --> 24:41.981
BLAKE WAS AT THE TOP
OF HER CLASS AT DILLARD.

24:41.981 --> 24:44.363
HER REFERENCES WERE IMPECCABLE.
I CHECKED THEM MYSELF.

24:46.155 --> 24:48.317
YOU CHECKED?

24:48.317 --> 24:50.820
SO YOU KNEW
WHERE SHE WAS FROM?

24:50.820 --> 24:52.992
YOU CHECKED
HER CASE RECORD?

24:52.992 --> 24:54.744
HER LOSSES?

24:56.826 --> 24:58.538
DID YOU KNOW THAT SHE --

24:58.538 --> 25:00.960
SHE WAS
AN EXCELLENT CANDIDATE.

25:00.960 --> 25:03.753
YOU WERE THE ONLY REASON
NOT TO HIRE HER.

25:05.424 --> 25:08.007
AND YOU DIDN'T FIND THAT
REASON ENOUGH?

25:19.769 --> 25:21.981
YOUR LABS ARE
WITHIN NORMAL LIMITS.

25:24.403 --> 25:25.945
THAT'S GOOD NEWS.

25:25.945 --> 25:28.277
I'M ON EVERY WEBSITE.

25:28.277 --> 25:30.239
GOT AN E-MAIL
FROM OUR BISHOP.

25:30.239 --> 25:32.241
I'M FIRED.

25:32.241 --> 25:34.153
SOMEONE'S THREATENING
TO BRING ME UP

25:34.153 --> 25:37.536
ON CHARGES
AS A SEXUAL PREDATOR.

25:37.536 --> 25:39.038
I'M DONE.

25:40.289 --> 25:42.371
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
A COMMUNITY.

25:42.371 --> 25:45.124
I MAKE ONE SIMPLE MISTAKE,
AND THEY DESTROYED ME.

25:45.124 --> 25:47.587
PUT IT AWAY.

25:47.587 --> 25:49.929
MY MOTHER SAW IT.

25:49.929 --> 25:51.931
HER FRIENDS
WON'T TALK TO HER.

25:53.673 --> 25:55.725
EVERYBODY'S TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT WHO THE WOMAN IS,

25:55.725 --> 25:57.977
AS IF IT'S
ANY OF THEIR BUSINESS.

25:57.977 --> 26:00.810
THANK THE LORD,
SHE'S OKAY.

26:00.810 --> 26:02.812
AT LEAST HER LIFE
ISN'T OVER, TOO.

26:04.063 --> 26:05.314
NOTHING IS OVER.

26:05.314 --> 26:09.358
IT'S DIFFERENT FOR US --
THE CLERGY.

26:09.358 --> 26:12.822
PEOPLE PUT THEIR TRUST
IN US -- THEIR FAITH.

26:14.323 --> 26:17.246
WE BREAK THAT TRUST,
IT STAYS BROKEN.

26:17.246 --> 26:18.908
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT.

26:18.908 --> 26:20.159
[ SCOFFS ]

26:20.159 --> 26:22.662
YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

26:22.662 --> 26:24.754
YOU CAN STAND UP TO THEM
AND HAVE FAITH IN THAT --

26:24.754 --> 26:26.876
HAVE FAITH IN YOURSELF.

26:28.087 --> 26:30.970
I HAVE TO BELIEVE THAT.

26:30.970 --> 26:33.172
THEY SAY HE DOESN'T GIVE YOU
MORE THAN YOU CAN HANDLE.

26:33.172 --> 26:34.974
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:34.974 --> 26:36.095
YOU SAY THAT,
ACTUALLY.

26:36.095 --> 26:36.926
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:36.926 --> 26:39.558
YES, I DO.

26:39.558 --> 26:40.640
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

26:40.640 --> 26:42.351
OW.

26:42.351 --> 26:43.723
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

26:43.723 --> 26:44.603
ARE YOU OKAY?

26:44.603 --> 26:46.065
MY STOMACH.

26:54.654 --> 26:55.695
NURSE!

26:55.695 --> 26:57.737
COMING!

26:57.737 --> 27:00.790
THERE IS A CLOT IN HIS CATHETER.
HIS BLADDER'S ABOUT TO RUPTURE.

27:00.790 --> 27:02.952
I NEED A SYRINGE
WITH SOME SALINE AND HEPARIN,

27:02.952 --> 27:04.503
AND PAGE DR. GREY --
NOW!

27:04.503 --> 27:06.245
RIGHT AWAY.

27:06.245 --> 27:08.457
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

27:08.457 --> 27:10.169
YOU'RE OKAY.

27:10.169 --> 27:12.551
April: THOSE NERVES
ARE GOING EVERYWHERE.

27:12.551 --> 27:14.754
HOW DO YOU BUILD SOMETHING
FROM THAT?

27:14.754 --> 27:17.556
[ SIGHS ]

27:17.556 --> 27:19.558
WELL,
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

27:19.558 --> 27:21.721
I THINK YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT HIM.

27:21.721 --> 27:23.312
HE'S GOOD.

27:23.312 --> 27:25.394
I KNOW.

27:25.394 --> 27:28.357
HE'S TALKING
ABOUT DIVORCE.

27:28.357 --> 27:31.270
WELL, YOU KIND OF SAW THAT
COMING, THOUGH, RIGHT?

27:31.270 --> 27:33.362
HE SAID "DON'T GO."
YOU WENT.

27:33.362 --> 27:34.864
ON SOME LEVEL --

27:34.864 --> 27:37.366
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.
IT'S NOT WHAT I WANT.

27:37.366 --> 27:39.158
I DON'T BELIEVE
IT'S WHAT HE WANTS.

27:39.158 --> 27:40.329
[ SIGHS ]

27:40.329 --> 27:43.042
I KNOW IT'S NOT
WHAT GOD WANTS FROM ME.

27:45.334 --> 27:48.207
WE'RE LOOKING AT A KID
WHO'S LOST HIS FAMILY,

27:48.207 --> 27:50.249
HIS HOME...

27:50.249 --> 27:52.671
MIGHT EVEN LOSE
HIS HANDS NOW.

27:52.671 --> 27:54.884
MAYBE GOD HAS
MORE ON HIS MIND

27:54.884 --> 27:57.757
THAN JUDGING WHETHER
YOU GET A DIVORCE OR NOT.

27:59.638 --> 28:02.301
DON'T YOU THINK
HE HAS BIGGER FISH TO FRY?

28:04.764 --> 28:06.976
Jackson: I'VE GOT ABOUT 60%
OF BONE STRUCTURE OVER HERE.

28:06.976 --> 28:08.067
HOW'S IT GOING
OVER THERE?

28:08.067 --> 28:09.268
Callie: [ GROANS ]

28:09.268 --> 28:12.361
I ONLY SEE
FREE-FLOATING DISTAL PHALANGES,

28:12.361 --> 28:14.814
AND SOME OF THEM
ARE ERODED BY TUMOR.

28:14.814 --> 28:16.736
Ben:
WE'RE APPROACHING THE CARPALS --
OR WHAT'S LEFT OF THEM.

28:16.736 --> 28:18.117
MM.

28:18.117 --> 28:20.079
I'M LOOKING FOR METACARPALS
OVER HERE.

28:20.079 --> 28:21.530
DO YOU SEE ANY VIABLE BONE
AT ALL?

28:21.530 --> 28:22.992
WELL, UH...

28:22.992 --> 28:23.913
DAMN IT.

28:23.913 --> 28:25.414
WHAT? WHAT IS IT?
TELL ME.

28:25.414 --> 28:28.828
JACKSON, I'M S-- I'M SORRY.
I'M JUST -- [ SIGHS ]

28:28.828 --> 28:30.669
THERE'S NOTHING HERE.
I --

28:30.669 --> 28:32.331
NO, NO, NO. WAIT.
JUST WAIT ONE SECOND.

28:32.331 --> 28:34.213
WELL, NO.
THERE'S NO BONE TO WORK WITH.

28:34.213 --> 28:36.175
I MEAN, LOOKIT.
LOOK RIGHT HERE.

28:36.175 --> 28:37.757
THERE'S FINGERS,
AND THEN THERE'S NOTHING.

28:37.757 --> 28:39.428
I DON'T --
COME ON. COME ON.

28:39.428 --> 28:40.259
JACKSON, I THINK --

28:40.259 --> 28:41.430
JUST WAIT, OKAY?

28:41.430 --> 28:42.972
I THINK
THAT YOU WERE RIGHT.

28:42.972 --> 28:45.394
I DON'T WANT TO BE RIGHT,
THOUGH. I JUST...

28:45.394 --> 28:47.106
LET'S KEEP GOING, PLEASE,
OKAY?

28:47.106 --> 28:48.187
YEAH, OF COURSE.

28:48.187 --> 28:51.190
[ MOTOR WHIRRING ]

28:51.190 --> 28:52.731
PUT THAT DOWN!

28:52.731 --> 28:54.613
[ WHIRRING STOPS ]
WE ARE WORKING HERE!

28:54.613 --> 28:55.945
WE'RE GONNA KEEP GOING
UNTIL WE ARE SURE

28:55.945 --> 28:57.446
THAT THERE IS
NOTHING LEFT.

28:57.446 --> 29:00.780
NOW, DO NOT PICK THAT UP AGAIN
UNLESS I TELL YOU TO.

29:00.780 --> 29:02.241
[ SIGHS ]

29:02.241 --> 29:03.492
Callie: JACKSON?

29:03.492 --> 29:04.914
I'M SORRY.
I WAS JUST --

29:04.914 --> 29:06.956
NO, NO, NO, JACKSON,
LOOK RIGHT HERE. LOOK.

29:06.956 --> 29:08.918
I FOUND SOMETHING.
I FOUND LUNATE BONE.

29:08.918 --> 29:10.960
THIS IS GOOD LUNATE BONE.

29:13.212 --> 29:14.713
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:14.713 --> 29:16.295
I THINK
HE CLOTTED HIS FOLEY.

29:16.295 --> 29:19.218
I'VE FLUSHED IT FIVE TIMES.
I CAN'T GET A NEW ONE IN.

29:20.509 --> 29:22.511
HE'S HYPOTENSIVE.

29:22.511 --> 29:25.384
GET ME A 50 cc
WITH A 14-GAUGE NEEDLE.

29:25.384 --> 29:26.886
YOU GOT IT.
HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

29:26.886 --> 29:28.437
I WAS DOING
A POST-OP CHECK,

29:28.437 --> 29:30.389
AND I SAW THAT THERE WAS BLOOD
IN HIS BAG.

29:30.389 --> 29:32.061
HOW LONG DID IT TAKE
FOR YOU TO NOTICE?

29:32.061 --> 29:33.772
I DON'T --
UH, WE WERE TALKING --

29:33.772 --> 29:35.484
YOU REALIZE
IF HE GOES INTO RENAL FAILURE,

29:35.484 --> 29:37.606
THIS WILL UNDO EVERYTHING WE DID
IN THE O.R. TODAY.

29:37.606 --> 29:39.608
DR. GREY, I DIDN'T MISS THIS.
I CAUGHT IT.

29:39.608 --> 29:40.990
IT SHOULDN'T HAVE HAPPENED!

29:40.990 --> 29:43.823
YOU FROZE IN THE O.R.,
YOU SCREWED UP HIS POST-OP CARE!

29:43.823 --> 29:47.536
IS THERE ANY PART OF THIS JOB
THAT YOU CAN HANDLE, BLAKE?

29:47.536 --> 29:48.908
I...

29:51.670 --> 29:53.212
GET OUT. YOU'RE NOT TOUCHING
THIS PATIENT.

29:53.212 --> 29:55.294
YOU'RE OFF MY SERVICE.

29:55.294 --> 29:56.215
GET OUT!

29:56.215 --> 29:57.877
NOW!

30:01.130 --> 30:05.094
Callie: ALL RIGHT.
THE HAMATE BONE'S INTACT.

30:05.094 --> 30:07.136
THERE'S THE TRAPEZOID...

30:07.136 --> 30:09.768
AND...

30:09.768 --> 30:11.100
THERE'S THE SCAPHOID.

30:11.100 --> 30:12.982
THAT MAKES
FOUR GOOD CARPAL BONES.

30:12.982 --> 30:14.393
WHICH IS NOT MUCH.

30:14.393 --> 30:16.315
AND ALMOST NO METACARPAL.

30:16.315 --> 30:18.697
BUT WE'D HAVE A BASE
FOR A PROXIMAL PHALANX,

30:18.697 --> 30:19.899
SO THAT MIGHT REGENERATE.

30:19.899 --> 30:21.320
HE IS YOUNG, SO --

30:21.320 --> 30:24.363
MAYBE WE COULD SCULPT THE BONE
AND GRAFT THE GAP IN BETWEEN?

30:24.363 --> 30:26.405
WE COULD WIRE THEM
WITH RIB GRAFTS.

30:26.405 --> 30:28.497
I MEAN, THEN I COULD ACTUALLY
MAKE SOMETHING OUT OF THAT.

30:28.497 --> 30:29.999
[ GASPS ]

30:29.999 --> 30:32.411
YES! LOOK! LOOK!
THAT'S A FIFTH METACARPAL HEAD!

30:32.411 --> 30:34.373
LOOK! RIGHT THERE!
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:34.373 --> 30:35.664
THAT'S A HAND.
THAT IS WHAT WE NEEDED.

30:35.664 --> 30:37.716
UNDER THERE, THAT'S --
THAT IS A HAND!

30:37.716 --> 30:39.258
WE GOT A HAND, PEOPLE!

30:39.258 --> 30:41.460
[ LAUGHTER,
CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

30:48.727 --> 30:49.929
WHEW!

30:49.929 --> 30:52.431
OH, MY GOD!

30:52.431 --> 30:54.773
WHEW!

30:54.773 --> 30:56.775
I CAN'T
FRIGGIN' BELIEVE IT.

30:56.775 --> 30:58.437
I DID.

30:59.688 --> 31:01.030
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:03.482 --> 31:06.115
SHE IS GOING TO BE FINE.

31:12.992 --> 31:14.543
AND YOU SHOULD TALK
TO HER.

31:14.543 --> 31:17.256
I DON'T EVEN KNOW IF I CAN
LOOK HER IN THE EYE NOW,

31:17.256 --> 31:19.298
LET ALONE TALK TO HER.

31:23.882 --> 31:26.305
30 YEARS AGO,
I HAD AN AFFAIR.

31:27.927 --> 31:29.929
I CHEATED ON ADELE.

31:29.929 --> 31:31.220
AND I HAD A DAUGHTER.

31:31.220 --> 31:33.142
I HAVE A DAUGHTER.

31:34.643 --> 31:37.896
ADELE NEVER TOLD LOIS OR ANYONE
ABOUT THE AFFAIR.

31:37.896 --> 31:41.020
SHE NEVER BASHED ME
TO HER FAMILY.

31:41.020 --> 31:44.233
SHE LIVED WITH THAT PAIN
AND EMBARRASSMENT FOR YEARS --

31:44.233 --> 31:46.325
ALONE.

31:46.325 --> 31:50.289
SHE PROTECTED ME,
AND I'M ASHAMED OF THAT.

31:50.289 --> 31:51.660
IT WAS A MESS.

31:51.660 --> 31:54.033
I MADE A MESS.

31:54.033 --> 31:58.127
AND FOR AS MUCH PAIN
AS I CAUSED AND FELT,

31:58.127 --> 31:59.959
I WOULD HAVE
NEVER BELIEVED

31:59.959 --> 32:02.541
THAT ANYTHING GOOD
WOULD HAVE COME OF IT.

32:02.541 --> 32:04.803
BUT IT DID.

32:04.803 --> 32:06.215
SHE DID.

32:07.806 --> 32:11.390
AND I AM VERY PROUD
TO KNOW HER.

32:19.688 --> 32:20.939
[ SIGHING ]

32:26.405 --> 32:28.117
YOU WERE RIGHT.
SHE DOESN'T BELONG HERE.

32:28.117 --> 32:29.738
SHE ALMOST KILLED
A PATIENT.

32:29.738 --> 32:32.031
SHE CAN'T BE TRUSTED --
NOT IN THE O.R.,
NOT WITH PATIENTS.

32:32.031 --> 32:34.073
SHE'S JUST DANGEROUS.

32:37.876 --> 32:39.168
SAY IT AGAIN.

32:39.168 --> 32:40.289
WHAT?

32:41.840 --> 32:43.542
I WAS RIGHT.

32:43.542 --> 32:45.174
I TRIED TO RISE ABOVE

32:45.174 --> 32:47.386
BECAUSE
IT'S THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

32:48.967 --> 32:52.141
BUT SHE HAS MADE
MISTAKE AFTER MISTAKE,

32:52.141 --> 32:54.853
AND SHE JUST IS
IMPOSSIBLE.

32:54.853 --> 32:56.515
[ WOMAN CLEARS THROAT ]

32:56.515 --> 32:59.018
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

33:01.520 --> 33:02.981
[ WATER RUNNING ]

33:02.981 --> 33:06.065
I'M SORRY.
IT'S THE TRUTH.

33:06.065 --> 33:09.368
SHE IS WORKING AT A HOSPITAL
THAT IS ABOVE HER SKILL LEVEL.

33:09.368 --> 33:11.200
I HAVE TRIED TO TEACH HER --
ALL DAY.

33:11.200 --> 33:12.741
I HAVE TRIED.

33:12.741 --> 33:15.074
OH, PLEASE.
YOU'RE BEING A BULLY.

33:15.074 --> 33:16.705
AND YOU'VE GONE OUT OF YOUR WAY
TO MAKE HER --

33:16.705 --> 33:18.877
YOU DON'T TEACH BY SHOVING
SOMEONE ELSE'S FACE IN THE DIRT.

33:18.877 --> 33:19.958
THAT'S NOT TEACHING.

33:19.958 --> 33:22.831
THAT'S JUST BEING MEAN
AND -- AND SMALL.

33:41.810 --> 33:46.605
♪ THERE'S A THOUSAND WORDS
THAT I COULD SAY ♪

33:46.605 --> 33:47.606
LEAVE ME ALONE.

33:47.606 --> 33:49.238
♪ TO MAKE YOU COME HOME ♪

33:49.238 --> 33:50.739
[ CHUCKLES ]
SINCE WHEN DO YOU PRAY?

33:50.739 --> 33:52.651
I'M NOT.

33:52.651 --> 33:55.154
OR TALK TO GOD
OR WHATEVER.

33:55.154 --> 33:56.995
I'M NOT TALKING
TO GOD.

33:56.995 --> 33:58.827
WELL,
YOU TALK TO TEQUILA.

33:58.827 --> 34:00.959
I'M TALKING TO DEREK.

34:02.121 --> 34:02.921
OH.

34:02.921 --> 34:05.164
OKAY, I'LL GO.

34:05.164 --> 34:06.965
I'M TRYING.

34:06.965 --> 34:09.218
I TRIED TO RISE,
I'VE TRIED TO TEACH HER,

34:09.218 --> 34:12.131
BUT I JUST...
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

34:12.131 --> 34:13.882
DON'T THINK I CAN.

34:15.974 --> 34:19.228
I THOUGHT HE MIGHT KNOW

34:19.228 --> 34:21.810
WHAT I'M SUPPOSED TO DO
WITH HER,

34:21.810 --> 34:24.103
WHY SHE'S HERE.

34:24.103 --> 34:26.775
I THOUGHT
MAYBE HE COULD TELL ME.

34:28.026 --> 34:31.570
SO, I'M JUST
GONNA SIT HERE AND...

34:31.570 --> 34:35.114
WAIT FOR SOME DIVINE
INTERVENTION OR WHATEVER.

34:35.114 --> 34:38.117
♪ WISHING
I COULD TOUCH YOUR FACE ♪

34:38.117 --> 34:39.958
♪ BUT THE TRUTH REMAINS ♪

34:39.958 --> 34:42.541
[ PATS BACK ]

34:42.541 --> 34:46.585
♪ YOU'RE GONE ♪

34:46.585 --> 34:49.128
♪ GONE ♪

34:49.128 --> 34:50.129
♪ GONE ♪

35:00.849 --> 35:02.521
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:08.897 --> 35:11.440
THEY LOOK LIKE HANDS.

35:11.440 --> 35:12.441
THEY ARE.

35:14.032 --> 35:15.534
THEY'RE YOUR HANDS,
BUD.

35:18.076 --> 35:19.868
THEY'RE REAL HANDS!

35:19.868 --> 35:21.240
[ LAUGHTER ]

35:23.912 --> 35:25.914
I CAN HOLD A BALL.

35:25.914 --> 35:27.506
Jackson: YEAH.

35:27.506 --> 35:30.169
TAKE A LITTLE BIT OF TIME,
A FEW MORE SURGERIES, BUT YES.

35:31.510 --> 35:33.212
WHAT DID WE TELL YOU?
HE'S THE GUY.

35:33.212 --> 35:34.092
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:36.134 --> 35:38.307
YOU ARE THE GUY.

35:38.307 --> 35:39.678
OH.

35:39.678 --> 35:40.809
Ben: AWW.

35:40.809 --> 35:42.221
[ LAUGHTER ]

35:44.523 --> 35:45.604
[ WHIMPERS ]

35:47.566 --> 35:49.648
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:54.323 --> 35:56.114
HE NEVER DID TELL ME
WHY THEY CALL YOU "BUMPY."

35:57.446 --> 35:59.578
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:59.578 --> 36:01.410
THERE WAS A DANCE
CALLED THE BUMP --

36:01.410 --> 36:03.702
BEFORE YOUR TIME --

36:03.702 --> 36:05.784
AND I EXCELLED AT IT.

36:05.784 --> 36:07.045
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

36:09.628 --> 36:11.460
YOU DIDN'T TELL HIM
IT WAS ME.

36:13.001 --> 36:15.003
WELL, I FEEL,
IF YOU WANT TO TELL PEOPLE,

36:15.003 --> 36:16.715
THAT'S YOUR DECISION,
NOT MINE.

36:16.715 --> 36:19.848
I'M SORRY. I'M STILL TRYING
TO FIGURE THIS OUT.

36:19.848 --> 36:21.300
OKAY.

36:21.300 --> 36:23.262
BUT FOR THE RECORD...

36:23.262 --> 36:26.225
I'D BE FINE WITH IT
IF YOU DID.

36:26.225 --> 36:27.976
VERY FINE.

36:30.148 --> 36:32.190
NOTED.

36:37.025 --> 36:39.027
[ MID-TEMPO FUNKY MUSIC PLAYS ]

36:39.027 --> 36:40.869
[ SNAPPING FINGERS ]

36:44.623 --> 36:46.585
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:46.585 --> 36:47.876
YEAH.

36:49.378 --> 36:50.329
APRIL.

36:53.001 --> 36:54.713
I, UH...

36:54.713 --> 36:57.175
I NEVER SAID THANKS
FOR BRINGING KAMAL.

36:57.175 --> 36:59.838
I'M SO SORRY FOR LYING,
BUT...

36:59.838 --> 37:02.761
GOD, YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
YOU DID FOR THAT LITTLE BOY.

37:02.761 --> 37:04.182
NO, NO, NO.
YOU DID IT.

37:04.182 --> 37:06.054
I MEAN,
YOU BROUGHT HIM.

37:07.306 --> 37:09.268
'CAUSE I KNEW
YOU COULD DO IT.

37:10.979 --> 37:12.271
OKAY.

37:12.271 --> 37:13.982
WE DID IT.

37:13.982 --> 37:17.195
JUST...THANK YOU.

37:45.934 --> 37:47.265
DO YOU WANT TO GO --

37:47.265 --> 37:48.266
Nathan: HEY.

37:48.266 --> 37:50.188
YOU READY?

37:52.851 --> 37:54.393
UM, NATHAN'S LEAVING
TOMORROW,

37:54.393 --> 37:56.234
SO BAILEY WAS GONNA
TAKE US OUT FOR DRINKS.

37:56.234 --> 37:57.356
SHE WANTED TO HEAR
WAR STORIES.

37:57.356 --> 37:58.857
YEAH.

37:58.857 --> 38:01.159
UM, BUT I COULD JUST TELL THEM
THAT I-I DON'T HAVE TO GO.

38:01.159 --> 38:03.532
OH, NO, NO. COME ON. YOU GUYS --
YOU GUYS GO CELEBRATE.

38:03.532 --> 38:04.903
WELL, COME WITH US.
YEAH, COME ON.

38:04.903 --> 38:06.244
I OWE YOU A DRINK.

38:07.576 --> 38:09.207
ANOTHER TIME.

38:09.207 --> 38:11.079
REALLY,
YOU GUYS HAVE FUN.

38:22.220 --> 38:25.133
♪ I THINK I DID IT AGAIN ♪

38:25.133 --> 38:27.185
I DIDN'T WANT BLAKE HERE.
I FOUGHT IT.

38:27.185 --> 38:28.767
THEN WHY DID YOU
HIRE HER?

38:28.767 --> 38:30.519
BECAUSE I'VE BEEN ACCUSED
OF CODDLING YOU,

38:30.519 --> 38:32.190
AND I DIDN'T WANT
TO DO THAT.

38:32.190 --> 38:34.523
I DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D WANT ME TO.

38:34.523 --> 38:35.524
THAT WAS ONE REASON.

38:38.276 --> 38:39.778
I DIDN'T WANT YOU HERE,
EITHER.

38:41.319 --> 38:42.611
WHEN YOU WERE ACCEPTED
TO THIS PROGRAM,

38:42.611 --> 38:45.574
I DIDN'T KNOW HOW I WAS GONNA
LOOK AT YOU EVERY DAY...

38:45.574 --> 38:49.658
AND BE REMINDED OF THE BEST
AND WORST TIMES OF MY LIFE.

38:49.658 --> 38:50.999
AND YOU WALKED IN,

38:50.999 --> 38:52.791
THE SPITTING IMAGE
OF YOUR MOTHER.

38:52.791 --> 38:55.544
TALENTED, SMART...

38:55.544 --> 38:59.297
HERE -- EVERY DAY.

38:59.297 --> 39:02.631
AND I DECIDED
THAT WASN'T FAIR TO YOU.

39:02.631 --> 39:05.384
I DECIDED TO PUT ASIDE
MY PERSONAL FEELINGS TO --

39:05.384 --> 39:06.765
RISE ABOVE.

39:07.806 --> 39:10.469
AND I'M GLAD I DID THAT.

39:10.469 --> 39:11.930
EVERY DAY.

39:14.232 --> 39:15.854
HE WOULD HAVE SAID
THE SAME THING.

39:15.854 --> 39:19.528
DEREK -- HE PROBABLY
WOULD HAVE EVEN LIKED HER.

39:19.528 --> 39:20.979
[ SIGHS ]

39:20.979 --> 39:23.241
♪ YOU SEE I'M A FOOL ♪

39:23.241 --> 39:24.863
♪ IN SO MANY WAYS ♪

39:24.863 --> 39:26.825
EXCUSE ME.
I'M LOOKING FOR A PATIENT.

39:26.825 --> 39:28.537
ROBERT MATTHEWS?

39:28.537 --> 39:29.828
ARE YOU HIS FAMILY?

39:29.828 --> 39:32.250
NO, I'M HI--
UH, WE WORK TOGETHER.

39:32.250 --> 39:33.452
OR WORKED TOGETHER.

39:33.452 --> 39:35.624
I'M THE CHOIR DIRECTOR
AT OUR CHURCH.

39:35.624 --> 39:37.756
OH. YOU'RE THE --

39:37.756 --> 39:40.419
OH. GOD.
YOU SAW IT.

39:40.419 --> 39:41.420
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

39:41.420 --> 39:43.091
WELL, I MEAN,
OF COURSE YOU SAW IT.

39:43.091 --> 39:44.923
ALL OF AMERICA SAW IT.

39:44.923 --> 39:46.595
OKAY,
HE DOESN'T DESERVE THIS.

39:46.595 --> 39:48.807
IT'S NOT FAIR THAT HE'S
ALL OF THESE AMAZING THINGS,

39:48.807 --> 39:50.308
AND --
AND THIS ONE MISTAKE

39:50.308 --> 39:52.100
IS ALL ANYBODY'S
EVEN GONNA THINK ABOUT HIM.

39:52.100 --> 39:55.313
LOOK,
CAN I SEE HIM, PLEASE?

39:55.313 --> 39:58.106
I WANT HIM
TO KNOW THAT...

39:58.106 --> 40:00.148
YOU KNOW,
HE'S GOT ME, AT LEAST.

40:00.148 --> 40:04.783
♪ GOT LOST IN THIS GAME,
OH, BABY ♪

40:04.783 --> 40:06.905
♪ OOPS, YOU THINK I'M... ♪

40:06.905 --> 40:10.789
THEY SAY SHAME CONTROLS
EVERY ASPECT OF HUMAN BEHAVIOR.

40:10.789 --> 40:13.331
♪ I'M NOT THAT INNOCENT ♪

40:13.331 --> 40:15.454
♪ OOPS, I DID IT AGAIN ♪

40:15.454 --> 40:17.586
IT'S ABOUT
WHO WE BELIEVE WE ARE.

40:17.586 --> 40:19.087
[ SIGHS ]

40:19.087 --> 40:21.339
♪ GOT LOST IN THE GAME ♪

40:21.339 --> 40:22.801
♪ OOH, BABY, BABY, OOPS ♪

40:22.801 --> 40:24.252
THIS WAS A MISTAKE.

40:24.252 --> 40:25.544
[ SIGHS ]

40:25.544 --> 40:27.135
I DON'T THINK
I CAN DO THIS.

40:27.135 --> 40:29.307
I DON'T THINK
THAT I WANT TO DO THIS.

40:29.307 --> 40:30.809
♪ I'M NOT THAT INNOCENT ♪

40:30.809 --> 40:32.681
I KIND OF WENT OFF ON GREY
ABOUT YOU.

40:32.681 --> 40:35.554
CALLIE...WHY?

40:35.554 --> 40:38.056
WHY ARE YOU
MAKING THIS HARDER?

40:38.056 --> 40:40.268
I DID WHAT I SHOULD'VE DONE
AT THE PARTY.

40:40.268 --> 40:44.022
♪ ...BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
THAT I'M SERIOUS ♪

40:44.022 --> 40:46.865
CALLIE, I GET IT.

40:46.865 --> 40:49.027
THEY'RE YOUR FRIENDS.

40:49.027 --> 40:50.699
HE WAS --

40:50.699 --> 40:51.910
YOU'RE A SURGEON.

40:51.910 --> 40:53.872
WE MAKE MISTAKES.

40:55.954 --> 40:57.455
WE NEED TO BE FORGIVEN.

40:58.627 --> 41:00.418
♪ I PLAYED WITH YOUR HEART ♪

41:00.418 --> 41:01.790
I WILL IF YOU WILL.

41:01.790 --> 41:03.792
♪ GOT LOST IN THE GAME ♪

41:03.792 --> 41:05.634
AND...

41:05.634 --> 41:07.586
[ SIGHS ]

41:07.586 --> 41:10.138
...[ Voice breaking ]
I'M HERE.

41:10.138 --> 41:11.259
IF...

41:11.259 --> 41:13.552
♪ I'M NOT THAT INNOCENT ♪

41:13.552 --> 41:14.683
...IF YOU ARE.

41:14.683 --> 41:16.725
♪ YOU SEE,
MY PROBLEM IS THIS ♪

41:16.725 --> 41:18.096
I'M HERE, TOO.

41:18.096 --> 41:20.599
♪ I'M DREAMING AWAY ♪

41:20.599 --> 41:22.731
BUT IN THE END,
YOU CAN'T HIDE,

41:22.731 --> 41:24.903
AND THE BODY DOESN'T LIE.

41:24.903 --> 41:27.025
♪ ...WATCHING THE DAYS ♪

41:27.025 --> 41:29.027
♪ YOU SEE I'M A FOOL ♪

41:29.027 --> 41:31.029
THE TRUTH IS RIGHT THERE
FOR THE WORLD TO SEE.

41:31.029 --> 41:33.491
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

41:33.491 --> 41:34.913
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:34.913 --> 41:36.324
♪ ...MY SENSES ♪

41:36.324 --> 41:37.415
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

41:37.415 --> 41:40.709
♪ THAT IS
JUST SO TYPICALLY ME ♪

41:40.709 --> 41:42.671
IT'S GREY.

41:42.671 --> 41:44.462
SHE WANTS ME ALL WEEK.

41:44.462 --> 41:46.384
HMM.

41:46.384 --> 41:47.966
SHE STILL WANTS
TO WORK WITH ME?

41:47.966 --> 41:49.798
♪ GOT LOST IN THE GAME ♪

41:49.798 --> 41:51.049
OR SHE STILL WANTS
TO RUIN YOU.

41:51.049 --> 41:52.971
[ LAUGHS ]

41:52.971 --> 41:54.182
YEAH.

41:54.182 --> 41:56.224
YEAH, IT'S DEFINITELY
ONE OF THOSE.

41:58.266 --> 41:59.017
COME ON.

41:59.017 --> 42:01.099
♪ I'M NOT THAT INNOCENT ♪

42:01.099 --> 42:04.272
OUR SHAME CAN CHOKE US,
KILL US.

42:04.272 --> 42:06.064
♪ ...TO YOUR HEART ♪

42:06.064 --> 42:10.528
IT CAN ROT US
FROM THE INSIDE --

42:10.528 --> 42:12.701
IF WE DECIDE TO LET IT.

42:12.701 --> 42:16.154
♪ YOU THINK
THAT I'M SENT FROM ABOVE ♪

42:16.154 --> 42:17.325
DON'T LET THAT HAPPEN TO YOU.

42:17.325 --> 42:19.417
♪ I'M NOT THAT INNOCENT ♪
